The paper deals with algorithms for preprocessing and querying weighted graphs, which is a fundamental problem in computer science. The use of spanners, emulators, and hopsets suggests that the paper may belong to the cs.DS (data structures) or cs.CG (computational geometry) sub-categories. The mention of distance oracles and approximation algorithms suggests that the paper may also belong to the cs.DM (discrete mathematics) or cs.NA (numerical analysis) sub-categories. Finally, the mention of weights and shortest paths suggests that the paper may also belong to the cs.GT (graph theory) sub-category.
